This paper is primarily focused on improving the wireless communication performance of vehicular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and control. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with optimization problems related to power allocation, which falls under the category of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses reliability and security issues, which could fall under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
